AWS Secrets Manager (recommended for AWS)

Store secret:

aws secretsmanager create-secret --name myapp/mongo --secret-string '{"username":"appuser","password":"S3cret!"}'


Grant least-privilege IAM to your EKS pod via IRSA:

Create an IAM role that allows secretsmanager:GetSecretValue for the specific secret ARN.

Annotate the Kubernetes ServiceAccount with that IAM role ARN (IRSA).

In pod, use AWS SDK to fetch secret at startup and cache in memory.



pseudo-code to fetch secret inside Node app:

const AWS = require('aws-sdk');
const sm = new AWS.SecretsManager({ region: 'us-east-1' });
async function getSecret(name) {
  const data = await sm.getSecretValue({ SecretId: name }).promise();
  return JSON.parse(data.SecretString);
}
